<br>
I still enjoy playing my MAs, especially my nanomage. I've slacked off a lot lately do to the mess known as 14.6.0 and PSO GC. <br>
<br>
My main complaint is we're now beginning to see some serious feature creep with the coming of 14.6 and Notum Wars. Previous experience in EQ would suggest that this is NOT good. Time will tell. <br>
<br>
I'll play until I can't stand the way things work. Not there just yet, but I keep a jaundiced nose out for anything even remotely smelling of the stench of creeping featurism. <br>
<br>
Besides...I always have my ENF...  &gt;=) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crimhawk>Crimhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Martial, Baby, MARTIAL.</span><br>  Posts: 446<br> <font color=#660000>(11/20/02 5:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2154.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: advice for new MAs</span><hr size=1> I've tried all profs at lvl 200 in the beta (where they are kind enough to give you lvl 200 and most of the uber equip you could ever want) and MAs just plain suck ass in PvP. No holes barred, MAs were the worst of all of the ones I tested. And with the advent of Notum, PvP is becoming more and more needed, esp if you are in a guild and wish to participate in it's activities. So I agree with the previous two posters......MAs have a bleak future in AO unless something is changed within the realm of PvP.<br>
<br>
