<br>
Yes, we do a LOT less damage in pvp now, but we still crit more often than other classes since we have uber crit buffs. If you throw in the fact that the damage being dealt will be thrown out by 6 people at a time, then the fact that we don't do as much as other folks won't be really noticed.<br>
<br>
I'd thought of giving up on my MA once 14.6 was released and they were touting the NW horn, until a guildmate told me that I should stop thinking of 1 on 1 fights and think of the largescale battles. THAT'S where the glory of the battlefield lay in the booster. In a place where our damage output is as much needed as the next persons.<br>
<br>
And if you try out NW and think an MA is still worthless in the pvp wars, then you'll just have to make a backup character that can get a super weapon on and see how well they do. <p>Bellerephon<br>
