<br>
It's great that you have resigned yourself to doing far less damage than pretty much every other class, but not all of us are as pleased with our new role as &quot;cannon fodder&quot;.  We would rather be able to actually impact the battle besides simply filling up position #6 in the team.  And that's assuming your guildies are nice and don't have another profession available to fight in that slot...cuz if they do, guess what?  You won't be in it.<br>
<br>
When the entire guild is reliant upon their tower(s) for the bonuses, there will soon be a return of the same issue we had when MAs were doing puny minimum damage against mobs in PvM...we will be passed over when teams are forming in favor of someone who can actually do damage in combat.  Go figure.  I'm going to presume you simply weren't around yet when that problem meant hours of standing around yelling &quot;LFG&quot;, and only being accepted into a team because no one else was available and (at that time) our regular crit buffs were castable on others and we were expected to sit back and spam team heals.<br>
<br>
I, for one, would prefer not to rely on pity from my guildmates or be forced to play the role of backup combat nurse and MoP buffer to keep me in a PvP team.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;Yes, we do a LOT less damage in pvp now, but we still crit more often than other classes since we have uber crit buffs.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Er, no actually...we DON'T.  Let's look at the facts for those who are using crit reliant weapons (take the ever-popular Ithaca shotgun, for example), and let's include the forthcoming scope nerf for us melee types, and assume all outside buffs possible (which is pretty much <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>de rigueur</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in PvP now anyway):<br>
<br>
PvP MA: 3% crit base, 24% UVC, 4% Take The Shot = 31% critical = 16% crit in PvP<br>
PvP Non-MA: 3% base, 15% scope, 7% Mark of Peril, 4% TTS = 29% crit = 15% crit in PvP<br>
<br>
Wow, I do 1% more crits in PvP!  Yaay!<br>
<br>
And if you wanna play the &quot;most players...&quot; game, such as &quot;most players won't HAVE a 15% crit scope!&quot;  OK, most MAs won't be able to cast UVC until level 193.  So let's look at the numbers using a Vision Enhancer/LMA in the mix:<br>
<br>
PvP MA: 3% crit base, 19% LMA, 4% TTS = 26% critical = 13% crit in PvP<br>
PvP Non-MA: 3% crit base, 8% VE, 7% MoP, 4% TTS = 22% critical = 11% crit in PvP<br>
<br>
I don't consider +2% crit all that &quot;uber&quot;, especially when our regular non-crit damage is so very very low.<br>
<br>
And let's not forget that the result of the recent PvP crit nerf is that most professions are now simply switching to newer NON-crit reliant weapons anyway, which do massive normal damage such as the X-3, Hellspinner, Manex Catastophe, and Queen Blade.  Well, guess what?  We MAs can't switch off our fists.<br>
<br>
The problem is based upon the fact that our fists are ABSOLUTELY crit-reliant.  A level 200 MA with a nearly 1200 attack rating will do, on average, about 250-350 pts with a normal hit in PvP.  Compare with an Enforcer with a beam hitting just as fast for an average of 3-4 times that at least, and let's not forget he has other Enforcer benefits (a ton more health than the MA, rage to ignore roots, etc).  It's only through our crits that we were viable in PvP at all.  And now they've taken that option away from us.  It is, after all, why increased critical chance is the class-defining ability of MAs.<br>
<br>
Face the facts...we're now the WORST profession for PvP in the game.<br>
<br>
To believe otherwise means you have either NEVER PvPed as an MA, or you are deluding yourself.<br>
<br>
- iccusion <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crimhawk>Crimhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Martial, Baby, MARTIAL.</span><br>  Posts: 448<br> <font color=#660000>(11/20/02 10:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2154.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: advice for new MAs</span><hr size=1> Oh yeah, I did make several beta chars and tried them out, comparing dmg outputs to my MA. All lvl 200, running their own respective buffs (no outside buffs), mostly the same equipment (Azure armor, crit scopes if they were provided, Globes of Suffering, custom prof rings, best ql weapons provided....blah, blah, blah, you get the point), and with every &quot;combat&quot; profession the MA got owned in dmg output. <br>
<br>
Yes, the MA got more crits on the average, but that dmg was nothing compared to the bursts, full autos, and enforcer brawls. Fixers, Soldiers, Enforcers, Agents, and NTs (I didn't make any pet caster profs or traders) ALL had much more superior dmg outputs than the MA. If other prof buffs had been added then the result would have been even more lopsided against MAs. Sorry, but with PvP becoming ever increasingly important to the game, MAs are left holding the short end of the stick.<br>
<br>
Even with MA weapons being used, most profs were able to outdmg MAs. Crits WERE our balancing feature in PvP....now we are just sad again.<br>
